	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Person_organization_arm  Entity: Organization 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Person_organization_arm.Organization">
		An <b>Organization</b> is an administrative structure in which persons are active.
	</ext_description>
	
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Person_organization_arm  Entity: Organization  Attribute: id 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Person_organization_arm.Organization.id">
	 the identifier that distinguishes the <b>Organization</b>. 
	</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Person_organization_arm  Entity: Organization  Attribute: name 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Person_organization_arm.Organization.name">
	 the text by which an <b>Organization</b> is known.
	</ext_description>

	<ext_description linkend="Person_organization_arm.Organization_relationship">
An <b>Organization_relationship</b> is a relationship between two instances of <express_ref linkend="person_organization:arm:Person_organization_arm.Organization"/>.
<example>
A team belongs to a department which itself belongs to a company. Such an organizational structure can be described up using instances of <b>Organization_relationship</b>.
</example>
	</ext_description>
	
	<ext_description linkend="Person_organization_arm.Organization_relationship.relation_type">
the string that specifies the meaning of the relationship.
<p>Where applicable the following values shall be used:</p>
<ul>
<li>
'hierarchy': The related Organization is a sub organization of the relating <express_ref linkend="person_organization:arm:Person_organization_arm.Organization"/>;
</li><li>
'legal succession': The related <express_ref linkend="person_organization:arm:Person_organization_arm.Organization"/>

 is the legal successor of the relating <express_ref linkend="person_organization:arm:Person_organization_arm.Organization"/>;
</li><li> 
'reorganization': The related <express_ref linkend="person_organization:arm:Person_organization_arm.Organization"/>

 is the successor of the relating <express_ref linkend="person_organization:arm:Person_organization_arm.Organization"/>

 due to an organizational transfer of responsibility. 
</li></ul>
	</ext_description>

	<ext_description linkend="Person_organization_arm.Organization_relationship.description">
 the text that provides further information about the <b>Organization_relationship</b>.
The value of this attribute need not be specified.
	</ext_description>

   <ext_description linkend="Person_organization_arm.Organization_relationship.relating_organization">
 one of the instances of <express_ref linkend="person_organization:arm:Person_organization_arm.Organization"/>

 that is a part of the relationship.
	 </ext_description>

